FBIS4-24358 "drafr126_a_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-126 Daily Report 29 Jun 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Zaire New Umbrella Group of Political Parties Formed New Umbrella Group of Political Parties Formed AB2906174094 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 1215 GMT 29 Jun 94 AB2906174094 Libreville Africa No. 1 French BFN [Text] A new umbrella group of political parties, comprising parties from the socialist and Lumumbist paths, has just been set up in Zaire. It is called the Union of Congolese Leftists [Union de la Gauche Congolaise]. According to lawyer Mukenge Ndibu, one of the creators of the movement, the left has an inactive military wing that can be easily mobilized with moral strength and an interest that only needs to be awakened, end quote. [no reference to opening quotation as heard]
